		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I liked it better than X2-3. Looking back it's still pretty nice, but I don't like the big characters, they're too big.</div>
<br />I agree 100%
<br />Bosses were so hard because both Mega Man and the Bosses were so large they took a significant space on the screen.
<br />
<br />Most bosses are hard to impossible to beat without their weakness, while on the NES games, using their weakness is doing it the "cowardly" way.
<br />Another issue is the quite a few things are ripped from older MMs. (Cloudman's stage is ripped from Air Man's for example).
<br />
<br />On the plus side, call me crazy or wathever but I like the music in MM7 much better than it in MMX series. I also like the style of game-play.

		

		</td>
